text.tspan: The Dode
Distribution: southern milkyway
Habitat: nitrogen lakes and electronic hills
Age: 42*10^18 seconds
Size: medium
Diet: electrons, in case of hardship neutrinos
Excrements: photons
Distinctive
feature: has only one nostril
The dode attracts potential mates by building a colourful dodecahedron,
a geometric form named after the dode. On top of photons it uses its
rainbow coloured tonngue to spread pheromones.
It likes nesting in metallic objects due to fear of mind control and
intergalactic dictatorships.
The dode was discovered in 2048 in the Tombough Regio by an expedition
team of the xHain hack+makespace. Further populations have been sighted
all over our solar system.
Lay(wo)men often confuse it with the dodo, a creature now extinct due to
unsuccesful attempts of creating dodocahedrons, which have proven to be
physically impossible to build.
